271—278. A curious passage, which some people have rejected, as it has been considered irrelevant, and 271—276 is wanting in many MSS.

The omission from the MSS. however is easily explained, as 270 and 276 both end with onus, and the copyist, having written 270, might easily carry on his eye by mistake to 277: a common source of error. Moreover the sense is really quite intelligible and defensible.
